Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.90,0:00:10.07,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kichijouji, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:14.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hachiouji, where Azuki is living, is still another thirty minutes away by train.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.27,0:00:16.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It really is far.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.31,0:00:27.41,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, he's in his first year of high school and it's summer vacation...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:30.83,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even Shuujin needs a change of pace.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But is he really doing the name?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.64,0:00:39.90,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma Eiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.85,0:00:42.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,There must be something I can gain from being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:12.63,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.63,0:02:13.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah–{\alpha&HFF&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.64,0:02:14.18,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah–Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:16.81,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Nakai, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.81,0:02:18.31,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Very nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.77,0:02:20.82,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of noisy, but come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:22.12,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.34,0:02:27.60,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Danger! Danger, watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.60,0:02:30.37,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-sensei, Mashiro-kun is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.72,0:02:33.69,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should give him a quick greeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.69,0:02:35.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.88,0:02:38.16,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Mashiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.16,0:02:40.16,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be helping out starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.16,0:02:41.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy to be working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.75,0:02:44.38,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, what's up Mechadoc?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.41,0:02:48.14,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Too old? Mechadocrow. Mechacrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.32,0:02:49.98,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's up Mechadoc?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.32,0:02:49.98,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL Note: This is a reference to an 80's anime/manga, "Yoroshiku Mechadoc."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.76,0:02:56.16,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei is always like that, except when he's eating or sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:58.86,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,And once he goes to sleep, he doesn't wake up for twenty hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:02:59.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:05.46,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Nakai-san, please quit calling Niizuma-kun "sensei."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.46,0:03:07.75,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You're seventeen years older than him, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.75,0:03:09.47,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,This is Fukuda-kun, he started yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.02,0:03:12.91,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,He placed twice for Tezuka, winning prizes both times
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:13.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fukuda...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.93,0:03:18.28,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,He's really skilled. Niizuma-sensei's editor is hoping to serialize him next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.54,0:03:21.38,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's him?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.53,0:03:24.28,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure he ran in NEXT! alongside me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.52,0:03:26.70,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Very nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:28.33,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.46,0:03:31.35,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's writing a name.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:33.93,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a fair amount of extra time here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.93,0:03:38.35,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,so Fukuda-kun is using it to write a name aimed for serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:39.77,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,He sure is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:41.68,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,The kid doesn't need three assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.16,0:03:44.77,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun even draws the backgrounds himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:47.97,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We basically just do fill-in inking, whites, and tone application.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:51.24,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But we're showing up, so we get paid assistant fees plus our commute and food expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.24,0:03:53.31,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,The working AC is nice too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.81,0:03:56.06,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You're better off working on your own stuff too, Mashiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.71,0:03:58.69,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun, what's your prize-winning history?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.69,0:04:01.70,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I haven't won any.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.70,0:04:04.47,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I ran in NEXT! once, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:05.05,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:08.29,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,In May; it was called "Kono Yo wa Kane to Chie."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:09.39,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,That was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:11.87,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,The fifteen year old genius, Ashirogi Muto?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.87,0:04:13.26,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,So Ashirogi's a pen name?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:14.32,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.32,0:04:16.10,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Another genius high schooler?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:18.60,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And a fifteen-year-old this time?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:20.58,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I lost in NEXT!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:24.76,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You ranked third, I was fifth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.76,0:04:27.24,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really glad an actual rival came.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.41,0:04:32.92,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Being able to draw "Kono Yo wa Kane to Chie" at fifteen is really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:35.06,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But it isn't really a good fit for "Jack."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:37.23,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,It was too bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.81,0:04:43.58,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,There's a limit to how long you can keep something with that depiction appealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.04,0:04:46.42,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If it ran in the main magazine, I don't think it'd rank high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:49.29,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Though I probably just sound like a poor loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:52.38,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But you can bet I'll be the poster boy for Jack in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:57.64,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Especially since in both Tezuka Awards I was in, Niizuka-kun got away with placing one prize above me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.64,0:05:00.77,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll be getting back at him with my pen... in the main magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.35,0:05:04.86,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,So that means the lowest guy on the totem pole here is Nakai-san, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:08.33,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He won the monthly prize just once about ten years ago, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.33,0:05:10.28,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to call Niizuma-kun sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.28,0:05:12.79,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,then why don't you call the two of us sensei too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.32,0:05:16.30,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.30,0:05:18.66,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But Nakai-san, you're working as a pro-assistant right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.30,0:05:20.63,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,A pro-assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:22.60,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,A full-time assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.60,0:05:24.14,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm still...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.14,0:05:26.95,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,So you're still thinking about serialization?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.95,0:05:28.44,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting any younger, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.44,0:05:30.46,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,And you're not doing anything in your free time, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.05,0:05:34.68,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Even Yuujirou-san told me he isn't hoping for anything out of you beyond being an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.26,0:05:38.35,Up of Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you this, I never want to end up like you, Nakai-san. {This is said under Saikou's line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.61,0:05:38.73,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do I have to work in a place with this kind of atmosphere?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:41.48,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I still haven't explained how we work yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:46.55,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,We pick up the manuscripts Sensei leaves on the ground and finish them with the fill-in inking and the tones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.55,0:05:48.87,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Then we return them to precisely where they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.87,0:05:50.12,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Things to be filled in are marked with an X.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:51.90,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,The tone numbers are written in blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.36,0:05:53.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:54.90,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Then take a seat over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:58.08,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait until Sensei puts the next manuscript down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:02.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Um, is it all right if I observe near Niizuma-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:03.95,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,No use doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.95,0:06:04.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No use?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:07.23,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He's different from a sensei with a wealth of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.23,0:06:10.31,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun isn't going to feel like teaching you a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.31,0:06:12.26,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he's going to teach me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.77,0:06:14.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.15,0:06:16.88,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Among the people here, Niizuma-san's drawings are the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:20.38,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't get kids these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:21.72,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,And they sure are cheeky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.72,0:06:22.42,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So are you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.49,0:06:25.26,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,You damn crow...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.96,0:06:29.40,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you my true power!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:31.81,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Zukyuun, perspective point! {This isn't a technical term. It's just something Eiji made up.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.07,0:06:35.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did he just decide where the vanishing point for the background should be drawn?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.14,0:06:43.29,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, you're slightly in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.33,0:06:48.38,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:06:57.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He said to pick these up, finish them, and then put them back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.36,0:07:00.83,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Ashirogi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.72,0:07:02.67,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:04.96,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Why're you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.96,0:07:07.29,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here as your assistant, Niizuma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:10.55,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Ashirogi-sensei shouldn't be doing things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.55,0:07:12.26,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to be drawing manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:16.53,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Well no matter what I draw, the story isn't done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.66,0:07:20.71,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you made "Kono Yo wa Kane to Chie"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.71,0:07:23.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi's the one who thinks up the stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:25.23,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mashiro, I do the artwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:28.20,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that how you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:31.52,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Then Takagi-sensei has some incredible talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:36.29,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. So while Takagi is making the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.29,0:07:38.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd try to learn something from you, Niizuma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.98,0:07:40.09,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,From me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:41.95,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything you {\i1}can{\i0} learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.95,0:07:45.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Probably... If you show me what you're drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.62,0:07:47.36,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Then please sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.36,0:07:50.43,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,This way it'll be easier for you, Ashirogi-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.43,0:07:52.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're the one who's a sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.01,0:07:56.94,Up of Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I'm thrilled we could meet again at a place like this, Ashirogi-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:59.19,Up of Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself at home. {This line and the previous one are said under Nakai and Fukuda's lines.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:55.83,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,They sure seem to be getting along well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.83,0:07:59.19,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I seriously don't get kids these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:03.70,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Which would you prefer, melon or chocolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.01,0:08:05.56,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Either one's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.56,0:08:06.31,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Then here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:08.70,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you think of my cell phone novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.16,0:08:11.91,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You've already written all this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:14.52,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! Just what I'd expect from an original manga author!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.26,0:08:17.87,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I can't do my own name...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.20,0:08:25.66,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Saikou ended up taking the assistant position...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.64,0:08:30.26,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it'd be weird for only Mashiro to be an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.26,0:08:31.75,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you two are a team...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.58,0:08:35.37,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I don't draw, so I couldn't go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.37,0:08:37.72,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Since the story's not done,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:40.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,it makes me feel better knowing he's doing something rather than just waiting around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.41,0:08:45.67,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Saikou's drawings could already pass as professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.35,0:08:51.06,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, what you said really was true, Ashirogi-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:54.05,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Becoming number one isn't that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:55.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Even with that first chapter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:08:59.34,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter one's rank was first, but chapter two's rank was fourth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.34,0:09:00.46,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,That was a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:04.53,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Fourth is still amazing. First chapters are usually on the covers and have color pages,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.53,0:09:06.20,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,so it's not uncommon for them to take first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.85,0:09:08.53,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Some people say that getting first with chapter one is a given,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.53,0:09:10.47,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,and the real battle starts from chapter two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.47,0:09:12.57,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Yuujirou-san said that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.92,0:09:16.46,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Bad works suddenly plummet down in the rankings at chapter two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:19.32,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,At fourth, you're within the popular mangas that already have animes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:21.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't be shocked to be there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.66,0:09:23.54,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,He told me that too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.54,0:09:27.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And Niizuma-san, you can draw manuscripts without even doing a name,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.09,0:09:29.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't think your rank is going to fall any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.67,0:09:32.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Usually, once you turn in names for the first three chapters at a serialization meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:34.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,you have as much time as you want to work on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:37.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So chapters four and beyond usually get harder,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.48,0:09:39.38,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't need to worry about that, Niizuma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:41.02,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.02,0:09:44.14,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,After hearing that from you, Ashirogi-sensei, I'm brimming with confidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:46.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'll be able to stay in the higher ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.71,0:09:49.41,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,and in a year you could get an anime adaptation and get first place again too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.41,0:09:52.65,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, an anime and first place? That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:53.64,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:55.60,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,At the rate you're going, your rank will go down!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.27,0:09:57.36,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Fukuda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:10:01.18,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be on the borderline by the tenth week, and in half a year you'll be canceled!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:03.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Canceled?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.67,0:10:05.80,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I read copies of chapters three and four,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:07.92,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the fifth there on the floor, and that's what I think!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:10.08,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Now I'm worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:12.54,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me see chapters three and four!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.66,0:10:15.44,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.17,0:10:18.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I think they're amazing as usual, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.58,0:10:23.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,That quality made me want to read the one-shot and chapter one quickly, all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:27.23,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But after reading chapters three and four, I've gotten used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.23,0:10:29.51,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So I kind of feel like it's getting less interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:32.93,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Amazing and interesting are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:37.35,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If the readers don't think it's interesting, the popularity will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.35,0:10:38.89,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.89,0:10:43.34,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe make it easier to understand so the readers can enjoy it more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.34,0:10:44.47,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.78,0:10:47.86,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,As a pro, you're not self-conscious enough, Niizuma-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.86,0:10:51.82,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If you just want to enjoy drawing for yourself, you'd be better off drawing doujinshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.82,0:10:54.40,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But the people who draw in Jack are pros.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:57.78,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You need to put the enjoyment of the readers first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:11:00.86,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Also, "CROW" doesn't have anything that appeals to the readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.35,0:11:04.33,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing more than cool, so people will get bored of it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:06.10,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing more than cool?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:07.95,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You went as far as calling him "Ashirogi-sensei."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.21,0:11:11.70,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,So you thought "Kono Yo wa Kane to Chie" was interesting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.70,0:11:12.80,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:17.82,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,That's because it raises the question to readers of whether money and intelligence...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:20.55,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,really are all that matter in this world, which makes it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.79,0:11:25.19,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, I may not have anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.19,0:11:28.19,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,The talent you have for drawing is certainly of a genius level.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:31.84,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But one might say that you're at a stage where only people who have read tons of manga,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:36.06,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,like the guys at the editorial department, would be happy and say "You're a genius!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.58,0:11:38.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You're incredible, Fukuda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.56,0:11:40.01,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You're going beyond the editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:40.65,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:44.47,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Most people aiming to become mangakas can do this kind of critique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:46.91,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But they can't draw an interesting one themselves. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.91,0:11:48.37,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:49.95,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:52.99,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,There are still two days until the deadline, so I'm going to rewrite everything from chapter five onward!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.99,0:11:55.46,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Please help me make it more interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:56.73,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:11:58.48,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.23,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Why would we help out a rival?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.41,0:12:03.20,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Your advice was extremely incisive, Fukuda-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:04.74,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, why—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.74,0:12:08.68,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Say, why was I giving advice in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.68,0:12:09.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:12.17,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:16.31,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try to figure out how to make "CROW" the best it can be!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.67,0:12:31.35,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Fine then, but just for chapter five.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.35,0:12:33.69,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We'll work together and give completely unbiased opinions of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.69,0:12:34.69,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You all right with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:35.73,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:39.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were kind of a jerk, Fukuda-san, but you're really a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.48,0:12:40.59,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a nice guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.71,0:12:43.20,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to change Jack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.20,0:12:45.84,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't want my rival to fall apart here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.84,0:12:48.88,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that sounds cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.64,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to change Jack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:12:53.31,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's make "CROW" get first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.31,0:12:54.55,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.55,0:12:55.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.65,0:12:57.69,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,What's with these guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:12:58.88,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Is it youth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:13:01.63,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,No, they have ambition and talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.48,0:13:06.29,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,So how can I make chapter five more interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.63,0:13:11.22,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It has had the same feeling to it since chapter one, so maybe you should switch things up a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:15.30,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Every chapter's all about what "CROW" does...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:19.82,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,More than half of new series end without even making it through the first year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.82,0:13:23.92,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,By the end of the first ten chapters, you can tell if it's going to be a long series.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.92,0:13:27.92,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, the major concern is keeping the reader interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.92,0:13:29.71,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Yuujirou tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.07,0:13:31.95,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Well no, he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:35.91,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He told me and I'm not even serialized, but he didn't tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.65,0:13:39.47,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just act like we're having meetings and you're writing names.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:41.28,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,He said that though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.02,0:13:44.28,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Yuujirou, always just doing whatever works!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:47.63,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean he has faith in Niizuma-san's talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:48.47,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.47,0:13:50.41,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,When I said I didn't want to do them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:53.00,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,he was kind of bothered at first, but we just ended up not doing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.86,0:13:57.23,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,An editor that doesn't have meetings and an author that doesn't draw names?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.23,0:13:58.89,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys taking manga lightly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.89,0:14:02.61,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,But it's like drawing the same thing twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.61,0:14:05.61,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,It takes all the tension out of it, it's a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:08.41,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Not having meetings or showing him names?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.41,0:14:11.11,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Then the editor can't judge if the thing's interesting or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.33,0:14:14.04,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,And you're asking "How can I make it more interesting?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:15.26,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to be screwing with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:16.45,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.68,0:14:20.70,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,So how do you think I could make it more interesting, Fukuda-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.49,0:14:24.45,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph, now you call me sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.45,0:14:28.32,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I first met you at the Tezuka Award award ceremony, Fukuda-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.32,0:14:32.07,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,That was before your debut in NEXT!, so I've been saying "Fukuda-san."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:35.18,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,But you've debuted now, so it should be "Fukuda-sensei."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:37.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does any of that really matter right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.18,0:14:37.38,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's a sensei after they've had their debut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.22,0:14:42.72,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Well in that case, the only one here who's not a sensei is Nakai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:45.50,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.70,0:14:50.43,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? I can't believe he said that, and he's laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.50,0:14:52.65,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:56.15,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You need to stop worrying about having fun yourself and start thinking about the reader's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:59.03,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the reader's feelings, huh? {adjust timing to include "Oh"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:15:02.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something more heart-pounding and exciting...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.73,0:15:06.13,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He's right! Make a proper climax in that chapter,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.13,0:15:08.65,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,and end it with some cliffhanger that'll make the readers want to keep reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.65,0:15:12.66,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh! Exciting, nervous, heart-pounding...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.71,0:15:16.21,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Climax! Cliffhanger! Unpredictability!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.21,0:15:18.06,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say unpredictability, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:19.56,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be something good to have, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.37,0:15:22.17,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is cliché.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:25.11,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Not like inking something black, but like something that reappears all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:25.11,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL Note: In Japanese, these two words are homonyms. Both filling in something without gaps and cliché are called "beta".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.11,0:15:28.71,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Like how cliché equals the opposite of unpredictability. Excitement too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.85,0:15:31.55,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,If you end it with the enemies beaten, it's always the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:37.58,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'll change the enemy character, make him stronger, but then make it turn out he's really an ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.90,0:15:39.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think that sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:42.83,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely cliché, but it's the kind of plot development that'll get the reader's blood pumping.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.27,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Standby! And the music starts!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.88,0:15:49.34,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just start off with the manuscript!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:51.53,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like names...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:53.11,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We told you, that's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.65,0:15:57.33,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We gave you advice, so we have a right to see if what you come up with is interesting or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:00.17,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Okay... I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:07.58,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Gacha-pinch!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.58,0:16:09.13,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Monster! {Only the last two bits have actual words in them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.89,0:16:13.75,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done. That was fast for nineteen whole pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:14.69,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:15.69,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's no use...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.69,0:16:19.58,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He did it too fast. I couldn't analyze what his thought process was or how he organized it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:24.08,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.98,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.13,0:16:29.28,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,True standby on the music!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.05,0:16:38.24,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,With all that advice, he did this much in such a short time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:41.28,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,He may be a genius in a number of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.94,0:16:43.95,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely surpass him though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:49.04,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,There's got to be something I can take from that kind of genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.81,0:16:52.69,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, you could probably do the whole thing on your own, couldn't you, Mashiro-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.88,0:16:57.16,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,From what I saw, you know quite a lot about manga. Believe me, I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:02.13,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,And if two people are doing it, that halves your income. I hear that can be tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:04.11,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're doing it together. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:07.35,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,My partner is far better at making stories than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.43,0:17:10.83,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm heading home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.34,0:17:15.42,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-sensei, it looks like you'll be redoing that whole thing, so I'm taking off for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.42,0:17:17.10,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be here at 3 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.10,0:17:20.70,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, okay! I'll be half done by then!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:24.81,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi-sensei and Nakai-san won't have anything to do until tomorrow afternoon either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:26.67,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,One more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:29.08,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the backgrounds to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.08,0:17:31.32,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,In the time it'd take you to do the scenery and the effects,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.32,0:17:34.42,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,you'd be way better off spending it thinking about what to do for the story. {QC: "you could spend more time thinking about what to do for the story."}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.42,0:17:37.93,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Mm... But I'm more of an instinct-type.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.30,0:17:43.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, believe that taking more time to think about the subject matter would make your works better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.74,0:17:45.85,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, you've got Nakai-san, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.06,0:17:49.67,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Nakai-san's been an assistant for over ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.08,0:17:53.20,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If you're just talking about backgrounds, he can draw even better than Niizuma-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:54.97,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,And his technique's not bad either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:56.61,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Nakai-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.83,0:17:57.85,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.85,0:18:02.32,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw anything or any place from any angle without any reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.32,0:18:04.74,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,And with effects, fill-in inked flashes or tone flashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.95,0:18:06.85,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm faster than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:10.85,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something to be proud of for someone who's trying to get serialized, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.54,0:18:16.17,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, I've got to go home and get to sleep. I've got a part time job too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.17,0:18:16.85,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Part time job?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.00,0:18:19.29,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, early mornings at a convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.22,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Being an assistant's not enough to make a living, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:24.88,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,But pretty soon, between the two jobs of part-time worker and mangaka, I'll only be one of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.88,0:18:25.44,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:27.13,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Good job today!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.13,0:18:28.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,From how he looks, you wouldn't think he's serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.94,0:18:30.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But he's really sticking to his guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:34.58,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma Eiji, Fukuda Shinta...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.58,0:18:36.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we'll be battling it out together for the top of Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:41.00,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But is it naïve to think that everyone will get serialized?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:43.59,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro-kun, want to go get something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.59,0:18:45.16,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:52.97,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have the steak set meal, the fried chicken from the side menu, a tuna capaccio and some french fries.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.97,0:18:57.07,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,And after that, a banana parfait and a cream soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.07,0:18:58.94,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,You can order whatever you want too, Mashiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:00.63,Main,Mashiro,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.97,0:19:03.33,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-sensei's a very generous guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.33,0:19:06.42,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we give him a receipt, we can eat whatever we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.42,0:19:07.61,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. {KmE: This wasn't on TL.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:10.74,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,So what about you, Mashiro-kun? Staying over tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:14.26,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'd planned on working all night when I came here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.26,0:19:16.47,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? You sure are young.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.47,0:19:18.95,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,You've got everything ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:21.68,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,We're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:25.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So he uses headphones at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:28.05,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Only because his editor told him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.01,0:19:31.50,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,There's a nap room, want to rest for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.50,0:19:34.96,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I think I'll watch by Niizuma-san's side a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.75,0:19:59.23,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be serialized...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:02.73,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,I–I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:07.19,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, somehow I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.95,0:20:10.97,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,It must be painful to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:12.73,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,S–Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.19,0:20:19.30,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It would probably be a little easier for me to get serious as a pro-assistant and take pride in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.05,0:20:23.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't want to throw away my dream of being a mangaka, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.09,0:20:26.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And yet I just drag myself around everywhere just being an assistant...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.31,0:20:29.57,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm already thirty-three...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:34.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what, don't be an assistant for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:40.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.88,0:20:48.23,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:20:49.55,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.65,0:20:53.06,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Crow, huh? Crow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:56.29,Up of Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Crow! Crow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:56.59,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,He's already done all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.29,0:20:58.51,Up of Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Black wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.20,0:20:58.51,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't put in any backgrounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.71,0:21:01.00,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,This might be worth doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.00,0:21:02.17,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:21:01.00,Up of Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Wings, wings, wings, wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.17,0:21:02.90,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.42,0:21:06.18,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Last three!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.70,0:21:13.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Incredible...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.06,0:21:16.84,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nakai-san can do undersketches for such complex backgrounds freehand,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.84,0:21:18.29,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and then ink it perfectly!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.92,0:21:20.10,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Crow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:25.33,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for all the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.33,0:21:26.44,Main,Nakai,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.53,0:21:27.50,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.50,0:21:28.57,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.79,0:21:31.41,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun, chapter five is... which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.41,0:21:32.83,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many I can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.83,0:21:34.95,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah sorry, it's not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.95,0:21:35.82,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.82,0:21:38.13,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Two days ago over the phone, you said it was already done...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.30,0:21:39.76,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I'm redrawing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:40.34,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.15,0:21:42.43,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the name for chapter five.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.61,0:21:43.47,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.62,0:21:44.93,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,You wrote a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.54,0:21:49.18,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?! This is incredibly interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.50,0:21:51.00,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,So it really is interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:52.80,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.86,0:21:56.23,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yuujirou-san, I'm sorry for being so cocky up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.23,0:21:59.89,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I'll do the meetings and draw the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.64,0:22:01.78,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,What brought this on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.01,0:22:05.26,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I think that from everyone telling me I was a genius so much, I turned into a goblin. {Well I can't make them have the same first syllable, but they both begin with "G" at least.} {QC} {TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.71,0:22:10.05,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Well, that way I can be a lot more relaxed about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.59,0:22:14.76,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,And now becoming the number one author in Jack really isn't just a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.97,0:22:16.71,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.71,0:22:19.27,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,For the early report of chapter three, you're third!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.63,0:22:21.25,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Even better than chapter two.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.51,0:22:23.66,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter three was better?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.66,0:22:25.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It was different from how we read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:27.79,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,I don't regret it though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.41,0:22:32.27,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,We made chapter five more interesting and got him to do meetings and names.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.14,0:22:39.08,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! I'm going to be the most popular mangaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:40.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was glad that Eiji was drawing names now too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.15,0:22:44.62,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I came here for Shuujin's sake.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.62,0:22:47.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've got to bring something back...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.42,0:24:17.39,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,It must be a pain drawing a manga with two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:18.89,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But together, we can get through things really quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.89,0:24:21.03,Main,Fukuda,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I'd always be getting in fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.03,0:24:22.96,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I trust my partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.96,0:24:25.00,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Jealousy and Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.00,0:24:28.01,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we're going after the same dream.
